-- FACTBOX: Attendees for G7 outreach dinner with banks
-- 
-- Fri Apr 11, 2008 6:21pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/04/11/us-g7-banks-idUSN1148342820080411

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - The U.S. Treasury Department on Friday provided the following list of attendees for an outreach dinner the Group of Seven is holding with representatives of global banks on Friday. The U.S. Federal Reserve declined to confirm whether they would participate in the meeting. 

 Private sector participants: Josef Ackermann, Deutsche Bank Herbert Allison, TIAA-CREF Win Bischoff, Citigroup Bob Diamond, Barclays Brady Dougan, Credit Suisse Laurence Fink, Blackrock Richard Fuld, Lehman Brothers John Mack, Morgan Stanley Yasuhiro Sato, Mizuho Corporate Bank Richard Waugh, Scotia Bank Officials: United States: Treasury Secretary Henry Paulson, Under Secretary for International Affairs David McCormick. Canada: Finance Minister James Flaherty, Bank of Canada Governor Mark Carney, Tiff Macklem France: Finance Minister Christine Lagarde, Bank of France Governor Christian Noyer, Xavier Musca Germany: Finance Minister Peer Steinbrueck, Bundesbank President Axel Weber, Thomas Mirow Italy: Finance Minister Tommaso Padoa-Schioppa, Bank of Italy Governor Mario Draghi, Vittorio Grilli Japan: Finance Minister Fukushiro Nukaga, Bank of Japan Governor Masaaki Shirakawa, Naoyuki Shinohara UK: Chancellor of the Exchequer Alistair Darling, Bank of England Governor Mervyn King, Stephen Pickford Russia: Finance Minister Kudrin ECB President Jean-Claude Trichet IMF Managing Director Dominique Strauss-Kahn World Bank President Robert Zoellick European Economic and Monetary Affairs Commissioner Joaquin Almunia Eurogroup Chairman Jean-Claude Juncker (Compiled by Mark Felsenthal)